description:
The investment seeks investment results that correspond (before fees and expenses) to the price and yield performance of the Beta Advantage® Emerging Markets Quality Dividend Index.
 The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in developing market companies included in the underlying index and the advisor generally expects to be substantially invested at such times, with at least 95% of its net assets invested in these securities. The underlying index is an equal-weighted index designed to represent a portfolio of approximately 50 companies in developing markets.
